Permafrost_thaw_P.html:<div class=""><h4 class="fw-bold fs-5 bg-primary text-light p-2">Permafrost thaw  « WGI,WGII »</h4><div style="width:97%;"><dd class="p-2 fs-6 border shadow ms-2 mb-3"><h5 class="fs-6 text-primary p-2">AR6 <button data-report="AR6" data-phraseid="2238" class="specificlink btn btn-sm bg-primary text-light" title="More information/Translation"><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i></button></h5><p class="fs-6 p-2 mb-0">Progressive loss of ground ice in permafrost, usually due to input of heat. Thaw can occur over decades to centuries over the entire depth of permafrost ground, with impacts occurring while thaw progresses. During thaw, temperature fluctuations are subdued because energy is transferred by phase change between ice and water. After the transition from permafrost to non-permafrost, ground can be described as thawed.</p><div class="p-3 small"><h6 class="fs-6">Parent-term</h6><ul class="items text-muted fs-6"><li><span class="specificlink" data-report="AR6" data-phrase="Permafrost" data-phraseid="517">Permafrost</span></li></ul></div></dd></div><div>	
